Comment 3: Turning right off Ennis Ave onto Royal Palm Drive, I've witnessed 4 accidents at this black spot myself plus many more very near misses.  How many other people's lives have to end or changed forever due to very dangerous intersection? I now avoid using this turning.
Comment 15: John: Lots of crashes lots of near misses
Comment 18: Sonia: Too many accidents with some resulting in fatalities. The last requiring a helicopter air lifting patient to Royal Perth who now is unable to walk. Drivers risk crossing onto or off of main road. Traffic backs up creating long wait times. Traffic lights would be more beneficial to the area rather than a roundabout considering we have a nursing home which amblulances visit frequently.
Comment 24: Phil: This intersection is notorious with accidents caused by the small opportunity to cross the 2 lanes due to speed of vehicles on the through road and the impatience of drivers trying to cross that have been waiting too long for a break in traffic
Comment 30: Andrew : Needs to have a overpass built to allow traffic to flow smoother and reduce turn hazard. As it becomes very busy and is hard to turn either direction onto and off the intersection
Comment 35: Natalie : Drivers turning off Ennis Ave too early and in front of oncoming traffic
